---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'North Macedonia Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/north-macedonia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Albania for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/albania' },
  { title: 'Greece for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/greece' },
  { title: 'Bulgaria for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/bulgaria' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'macedoniaFit', header: 'N. Macedonia Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MKD$29,000-41,400/mo', macedoniaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MKD$33,900-48,400/mo', macedoniaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MKD$26,100-37,250/mo', macedoniaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MKD$24,200-34,600/mo', macedoniaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Triglav, Sava)', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'MKD$5,000-12,000/mo', macedoniaFit: 'Basic' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'MKD$26,100-41,400', annual: 'MKD$313,200-496,800' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'MKD$35,800-55,200', annual: 'MKD$429,600-662,400' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'MKD$48,150-74,100', annual: 'MKD$577,800-889,200' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'MKD$1,000-3,000/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'MKD$5,000-15,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in North Macedonia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in North Macedonia. Lake Ohrid beauty, affordable Balkans living, EU candidate, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in North Macedonia"
  subheadline="North Macedonia offers stunning Lake Ohrid, affordable Balkans living, warm hospitality, and EU candidate status—an emerging retirement destination with natural beauty and low costs."
  heroImage="/images/countries/north-macedonia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose North Macedonia</h2>
  <p>
    North Macedonia offers stunning Lake Ohrid (UNESCO), affordable living, warm hospitality, and improving infrastructure as EU candidate. For budget-conscious retirees seeking Balkans beauty with low costs, North Macedonia provides excellent value with natural attractions.
  </p>

  <p>
    Skopje is the capital with best healthcare and modern amenities. Ohrid offers lakeside lifestyle and cultural heritage. Bitola has Ottoman charm. Most expats choose Skopje for healthcare or Ohrid for lifestyle; prices low throughout country.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Improving; private options in Skopje</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Macedonian; some English; Albanian in west</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> MKD$35,000-70,000/month (~$620-1,240 USD); very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Continental; Mediterranean influence south</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Hospitable; multicultural; EU aspirations</li>
      <li><strong>Natural beauty:</strong> Lake Ohrid; mountains; national parks</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">North Macedonia Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    North Macedonia healthcare is improving—Sistina Hospital and Acibadem (Turkish chain) in Skopje provide modern private care. Public system functional but underfunded. Complex cases may need Thessaloniki (Greece, 3 hours) or Sofia (Bulgaria, 4 hours) for specialists.
  </p>

  <p>
    EU accession process driving healthcare improvements. Private care in Skopje is affordable. International insurance with Greece/Bulgaria coverage recommended for regional access to EU-standard care.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Regional EU Access</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Greece and Bulgaria provide EU-standard medical backup—Thessaloniki is 3 hours from Skopje, Sofia is 4 hours. Include EU countries in insurance coverage. Local care handles routine needs; regional EU access provides specialist backup.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    North Macedonia has accessible visa policies:
  </p>

  <h3>Visa-Free Entry</h3>
  <p>
    90 days visa-free for EU, US, UK, and many nationalities. Very accessible for exploration.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Stay</h3>
  <p>
    Extensions available beyond 90 days. Apply through local police stations.
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Residence</h3>
  <p>
    For stays over 90 days. Various categories including retirement and property ownership.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residence</h3>
  <p>
    After 5 years legal residence. North Macedonia welcomes foreign residents.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for North Macedonia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Include Greece/Bulgaria coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for North Macedonia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with EU coverage (especially Greece/Bulgaria) essential. Skopje private hospitals handle routine care. Regional EU access provides specialist backup. Local insurance has age limits. EU-focused coverage recommended.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in North Macedonia, EU evacuation coverage important:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for North Macedonia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Europe network, Balkans coverage</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Greece access:</strong> EU healthcare 3 hours away</li>
    <li><strong>Affordable living:</strong> Stretch retirement income</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with EU evacuation benefits.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for North Macedonia (MKD ~56.5 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Skopje base:</strong> Best private healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Regional network:</strong> Greece/Bulgaria for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>Budget lifestyle:</strong> Low living costs stretch budget</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Lake Ohrid Enthusiast, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,000/month pension. Lakeside lifestyle. Ohrid.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Europe focus.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MKD$32,000/month (~$565). UNESCO beauty; Skopje backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Balkans Explorer, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €1,800/month pension. Regional travel. Skopje base.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with comprehensive Balkans coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MKD$38,000/month (~$670). Regional mobility; Greek backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Budget Maximizer, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,400/month income. Maximum stretch. Bitola.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with essential coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MKD$26,100/month (~$460). Ottoman charm; Thessaloniki accessible.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is North Macedonia safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very safe—low crime. Stable since 2001 resolution. EU candidate status brings stability focus. Safe for walking. Some political demonstrations occasionally but peaceful. Overall very secure retirement destination.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Macedonian?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Helpful but not essential—Macedonian is Slavic language. English spoken by younger generation, in tourism areas, and private healthcare. Some Albanian in western regions. Learning basics appreciated. Similar to Bulgarian/Serbian.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's Lake Ohrid like?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Stunning—UNESCO World Heritage for natural and cultural value. Europe's oldest lake. Crystal clear water. Byzantine churches. Ohrid town is charming. Swimming, boating, relaxation. Four-season destination. Premier attraction.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about EU membership?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        EU candidate since 2005—accession negotiations ongoing. Name change agreement with Greece (2019) removed major obstacle. NATO member since 2020. EU membership likely eventual but timeline uncertain. Infrastructure improving in anticipation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for North Macedonia coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with North Macedonia authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
